caption: Sex Discrimination
created: 20260405120000000
modified: 20260405120000000
title: Policy4161(s1)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

''Sex discrimination'' occurs when a person, because of the person's sex, is denied participation in or the benefits of any education program or activity receiving federal financial assistance. This includes discrimination on the basis of sex stereotypes, sex characteristics, pregnancy or related conditions, sexual orientation, and gender identity. ''__Sex discrimination includes sex-based harassment__'', as defined below.
